claim.claim-text:
1. A bottled water dispenser, comprising:
a) a cabinet having upper and lower end portions;
b) an unpressurized reservoir contained within the cabinet, the reservoir containing water with a water surface;
c) a diffuser that occupies the reservoir, for emitting bubbles into the reservoir:
d) one or more spigots on the cabinet for dispensing water from the reservoir;
e) an ozone generator housing positioned next to the cabinet, said housing having an ozone generator inside the housing;
f) air flow lines for transmitting air between the ozone generator and the diffuser; and
g) a pump that pumps air from the housing to the diffuser via the flow lines; and
h) wherein the pump output is between about 1-10 liters per minute and the diffuser has a median pore size of 10-60 microns.

13. A bottled water dispenser, comprising:
a) a cabinet having upper and lower end portions;
b) a reservoir contained within the cabinet, the reservoir containing water with a water surface;
c) a diffuser that occupies the reservoir, for emitting bubbles into the reservoir:
d) one or more spigots on the cabinet for dispensing water from the reservoir;
e) an ozone generator housing positioned next to the cabinet, said housing having an ozone generator inside the housing;
f) air flow lines for transmitting air between the ozone generator and the diffuser; and
g) a pump that pumps air from the housing to the diffuser via the flow lines;
h) wherein the pump output is between about 1-10 liters per minute; and
i) wherein the diffuser is of a material that has pores and pore channels and wherein the pore channels have a spacing that prevents bubble stream lateral coalescing over about 10-35% of surface area.

14. A bottled water dispenser, comprising:
a) a cabinet having upper and lower end portions;
b) a reservoir contained within the cabinet, the reservoir containing water with a water surface;
c) a diffuser that occupies the reservoir, for emitting bubbles into the reservoir:
d) one or more spigots on the cabinet for dispensing water from the reservoir;
e) an ozone generator housing positioned next to the cabinet, said housing having an ozone generator inside the housing;
f) air flow lines for transmitting air between the ozone generator and the diffuser; and
g) a pump that pumps air from the housing to the diffuser via the flow lines;
h) wherein the pump output is between about 1-10 liters per minute; and
i) wherein the diffuser is of a low pressure diffuser material veneered with high surface energy to water interfacial tension ratios for generating smaller bubbles.
